issue.title: Is there a way to sample overrides EventHub messages and send events?
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I've tried to do sample override for EventHub messages but I wasn't able to do so. I can't find any documentation example allowing me to do so. I've tried attributes like `messaging.system` strict to `eventhubs` and `servicebus`, and even `net.peer.name` strict targetting the eventhub connection string hostname in question.

**Describe the solution you would like**
Users would be able to do sample overrides for EventHub dependencies.

**Describe alternatives you have considered**
I've considering using different fields to filter the dependency like az.namespace strict to `Microsoft.EventHub`. I've collected available attributes from the debug log but they don't seem to work for this telemetry type.

**Additional context**
I'm using AppInsights Java 3.4.12.

issue.title: Event Hub SDK instrumentation not emitting 'EventHubs.Process' after upgrade from 4.3.9-> 4.3.10
issue.body:
### Expected behavior
When using Azure EH SDK version 

### Actual behavior
Describe what actually happened that was unexpected.

### To Reproduce

Using the following dependencies: 
```xml
		<dependency>
			<groupId>com.azure</groupId>
			<artifactId>azure-messaging-eventhubs</artifactId>
			<version>5.15.3</version>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>com.azure</groupId>
			<artifactId>azure-messaging-eventhubs-checkpointstore-blob</artifactId>
			<version>1.16.3</version>
		</dependency>

		<dependency>
			<groupId>com.microsoft.azure</groupId>
			<artifactId>applicationinsights-runtime-attach</artifactId>
			<version>3.4.10</version>
		</dependency>
```

with this EH client setup:
```java
		var clientBuilder = new EventProcessorClientBuilder()
			.consumerGroup(eventHubConfig.getConsumerGroup())
			.checkpointStore(checkpointStore)
			.processEvent(this::processEvent)
			.processError(errorProcessor)
			.processPartitionInitialization(this::processPartitionInitialization)
			.processPartitionClose(this::processPartitionClose)
			.trackLastEnqueuedEventProperties(true);
```

when we were using 4.3.9, we saw requests of `name=EventHubs.Process` but after upgrading to 4.3.10, we no longer get any of these. Other app code and config is the same. 

### System information
Please provide the following information:
 - SDK Version: 4.3.10
 - OS type and version: Docker/Linux
 - Application Server type and version (if applicable):
 - Using spring-boot? Yes
 - Additional relevant libraries (with version, if applicable):

### Logs


### Screenshots
Our instrumentation showing the EventHub dependencies compared to our manually emitted dependencies by AI SDK version:
![image](https://github.com/microsoft/ApplicationInsights-Java/assets/1774478/a2a97479-652b-4cb7-b972-cb78789b9090)

issue.title: CVE-2023-4586
issue.body:
We've seen [CVE-2023-4586](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-4586) flagged in the App Insights agent JAR by the Aqua security scanner in our environment at Swiss Re.

This is one of those CVEs where the project owners disagree that it is a CVE and there's no plan to fix on the current Netty 4 version. The suggested 'fix' of upgrading to Netty 5 makes no sense since they've never released this version.

I saw you have upgraded the Netty dependency to 4.1.100, but this won't fix the above CVE. The reported CVE was originally listed as impacting all versions less than 4.1.100, but this has since been updated to say 'less than 5.0.0'.

comment.body:
Hi

I'm in discussion with the Swiss Re Vulnerability Management team on how we can get this CVE dealt with centrally. I am hoping they agree that this CVE can be ignored or at least suspended for a period of time. Also fingers-crossed that the CVE either gets downgraded or modified as I imagine this is causing a headache for many teams globally.
